2 HOUSE BILL 680
1 3–402.
2 This subtitle does not apply to a municipal corporation that:
3 (1) [does not require voter registration for its elections;
4 (2)] prior to January 1, 1990, used the voter registry supplied by the local
5 board as qualification for voting in municipal elections; or
6 [(3)] (2) provides for the local board to conduct municipal elections.
7 3–403.
8 (a) A voter residing in a municipal corporation is considered to be registered for
9 elections in that municipal corporation if the voter is included on the statewide voter
10 registration list at an address within the municipal corporation.
11 (g) This section may not be construed to prohibit a municipal corporation from
12 administering and maintaining a supplemental list of those individuals who are not on the
13 statewide voter registration list but who may otherwise be qualified to register to vote with
14 the municipal corporation.
15 Article – Local Government
16 4–108.6.
17 (A) EACH MUNICIPALITY SHALL REQUIRE VOTER REGISTRATION FOR ITS
18 ELECTIONS.
19 (B) AN INDIVIDUAL MAY NOT BECOME REGISTERED TO VOTE IN A
20 MUNICIPAL ELECTION IF THE INDIVIDUAL IS NOT A CITIZEN OF THE UNITED STATES.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2025.

